cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the allocation of resources in IoT devices, which is a networking and architecture-related problem. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The allocation of resources in IoT devices can be seen as a distributed computing problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the allocation of resources in a system (IoT device) to optimize the performance of services, which is a systems and control problem. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the allocation of resources to services, which can be seen as an information theory problem. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The algorithms developed in the paper to approximate the optimal solution can be seen as AI-related.
